**Describe your issue**
Custom plugin
```js
const plugin = require('tailwindcss/plugin')
const iconComponent = plugin(function ({matchComponents}) {
  matchComponents({
      icon: (value) => ({
        maskImage: `url('../img/icons/${value}.svg')`
      })
    },
  )
})
module.exports = iconComponent
```
HTML
```html
<div class="icon-[search]"></div><!--does not process-->
<div class="after:icon-[search]"></div><!--process ok-->
<div class="before:icon-[search]"></div><!--process ok-->
```
Result CSS
```css
.icon-\[search\] {
  -webkit-mask-image: url(../img/icons/search.svg);
  mask-image: url(../img/icons/search.svg)
}

.after\:icon-\[search\]:after {
  content: var(--tw-content);
  -webkit-mask-image: url(/assets/v1/img/icons/search-9ccc80b4.svg);
  mask-image: url(/assets/v1/img/icons/search-9ccc80b4.svg)
}

.before\:icon-\[search\]:before {
  content: var(--tw-content);
  -webkit-mask-image: url(/assets/v1/img/icons/search-9ccc80b4.svg);
  mask-image: url(/assets/v1/img/icons/search-9ccc80b4.svg)
}
```

As you can see, the url function in the class "icon-[search]" did not pass the correct processing

